### Get all work orders (should now have 3)
GET http://localhost:5141/work-orders

### Get work orders for specific equipment (e.g., Equipment ID 1)
GET http://localhost:5141/work-orders/equipment/1

### Get single work order (e.g., ID 1)
GET http://localhost:5141/work-orders/1

### Update work order (e.g., ID 1)
PUT http://localhost:5141/work-orders/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Belt slipping - URGENT",
  "description": "Needs immediate tension adjustment",
  "assignedTo": "John Smith"
}

### Complete work order (this updates equipment maintenance dates!)
POST http://localhost:5141/work-orders/1/complete

### Verify equipment maintenance dates were updated
GET http://localhost:5141/equipment/1

### Delete work order (e.g., ID 1)
DELETE http://localhost:5141/work-orders/1